The Java Regex or Regular expression is an API to define pattern for searching and manipulating strings.
It is widely used to define constraint on strings such as password and email validation.

Java Regex API provides 1 interface and 3 classes in java.util.regex package.

java.util.regex.package.
It provides following classes and interface for regurlar experssion.
----------------------------------
The Matcher and Pattern classes are widely used in java regular experession .
1.MatchResult Interface
___________________________________________________
2.Matcher class
___________________________________________________
.boolean matches() //test whether the regular experssion matches the pattern.
.boolean find() // find the next experession that matches the pattern.
.boolean  find(int start)  // find the next expression that matches the pattern from the given start number.
.int end() // return an end index.

3.Pattern class
___________________________________________________
.static pattern compile(String regex) // compile the given regex and return the instance of pattern
.Matcher matcher(CharSequence input).  // creates a matcher that matches the given input with pattern.
.static boolean matches(String regex, CharSequence input)  // it works as the combination of compile and matcher methods. it compiles the regular expression and matches the given input with the pattern.
.String [] split(CharSequence input)   // splits the given input string around matches of given pattern.
.String pattern () return the regex pattern.
4.PatternSyntaxException class.

